HB 189 Original 2026 Regular Session Newell
Abstract: Authorizes state supplemental pay for fire protection officers employed by the
Lakefront Management Authority
Present law provides state supplemental pay of $600 per month for fire protection officers
employed full-time by any municipality, parish, fire protection district, or other political
subdivision maintaining a fire department, or by the Chitimacha Tribe of Louisiana or the
Coushatta Tribe of Louisiana, or by any nonprofit corporation contracting with any such
political subdivisions to provide fire protection services. Also provides state supplemental
pay of $600 per month to fire protection officers employed full-time by the New Orleans
Port Authority, Plaquemines Port Harbor and Terminal District, and the Port of South
Louisiana.
Proposed law retains present law and adds full-time fire protection officers of the Lakefront
Management Authority to the list of fire protection officers authorized to receive state
supplemental pay of $600 per month.
Effective if and when the proposed amendment of Article X of the Constitution of La.
contained in the Act which originated as House Bill No. ___ of this 2026 Regular Session
of the Legislature is adopted at a statewide election and becomes effective.
(Adds R.S. 40:1666.1(A)(8))
